    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "PAN AMERICAN WORLD AIRWAYS",
      "A24073 - A sleek, triple-tailed Pan American World Airways Clipper wings over a residential section\nof New York City as it heads out to sea at the start of a trans-Atlantic flight between Europe and\nthe United States.",
      "1946\nTRIP TIMES WERE GREATLY REDUCED WHEN THE 300-MILE-AN-HOUR\nLOCKHEED CONSTELLATION-TYPE CLIPPER JOINED THE PAA FLEET IN 1946.\nWINGSPPEAD TS 123-\nTHIS PLANE CARRIED 56 FIRST-CLASS PASSENGERS. WINGSPREAD IS 123-\nFEET; LENGTH 95-FEET -3-INCHES. POWER PLANT WAS OF FOUR WRIGHT\nCYCLONE ENGINES OF 2, 200-HORSEPOWER BACH WITH AN OPERATING RANGE OF\n8\n3,500-MILES."
    ],
